quran[31]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,40,"[Who will be] in gardens, questioning each other"
  74,41,"About the criminals,"
  74,42,"[And asking them], "
  75,37,"Had he not been a sperm from semen emitted?"
  75,38,"Then he was a clinging clot, and [Allāh] created [his form] and proportioned [him]"
  75,39,"And made of him two mates, the male and the female."
  76,31,"He admits whom He wills into His mercy; but the wrongdoers - He has prepared for them a painful punishment."
  77,28,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  77,29,"[They will be told], "
  77,30,"Proceed to a shadow [of smoke] having three columns."
  78,25,"Except scalding water and [foul] purulence -"
  78,26,"An appropriate recompense.{1}",footnotes:1:[In proportion to and comparable with their crimes.]
  78,27,"Indeed, they were not expecting an account"
  79,19,"And let me guide you to your Lord so you would fear [Him]?'"
  79,20,"And he showed him the greatest sign,{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., the miracle of his staff becoming a great snake.]
  79,21,"But he [i.e., Pharaoh] denied and disobeyed."
  80,16,"Noble and dutiful."
  80,17,"Destroyed [i.e., cursed] is man;{1} how disbelieving is he.",footnotes:1:[i.e., those who deny Allāh's message.]
  80,18,"From what thing [i.e., substance] did He create him?"
  81,13,"And when Paradise is brought near,"
  81,14,"A soul will [then] know what it has brought [with it].{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., all of one's deeds from worldly life, which have accompanied the soul to the Hereafter.]
  81,15,"So I swear by the retreating stars -"
  82,7,"Who created you, proportioned you, and balanced you?"
  82,8,"In whatever form He willed has He assembled you."
  82,9,"No! But you deny the Recompense."
  83,4,"Do they not think that they will be resurrected"
  83,5,"For a tremendous Day -"
  83,6,"The Day when mankind will stand before the Lord of the worlds?"
  84,1,"When the sky has split [open]"
  84,2,"And has listened [i.e., responded]{1} to its Lord and was obligated [to do so]",footnotes:1:[It will have heard Allāh's command and will have inclined immediately to compliance and willing obedience.]
  84,3,"And when the earth has been extended{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., stretched flat and spread out.]
